\cf0 	Excerpt from the journal of Nicholas Piwhall dated January twentieth 1249:\

\fs18 Age:12
\fs26 	
\f1 I have mentioned previously the art which I am studying. but I have not yet described it in depth.  Everything is made from the Four Elements:  Earth, Water, Air, and Fire.  The goal in alchemy is to adjust the amount of each element in a common metal to produce gold.  We are also hunting for Thaliksir, the fabled elixir of life.  A hunt for the Philosopher's Stone, and object said to aid us in our quest, continues.  My master, William Ralc, leaves next week to aid in the search and will not be back for another month, leaving me in the care of Sir Radi, one of his closest friends.  I hope he will be one of mine as well.\
