\cf0 	Sir Radi's mansion was the kind of house you could look at and think is massive, but is really not that big.  Sure it had five floors (basement/cellar, ground floor, second story, third story, attic), and it was much bigger than the home of the peasants and vassals, but it was relatively small for a mansion and absolutely tiny compared to some manor houses.  And although his house was twice the size of Sir Radi's, Nicholas found no trouble getting comfortable.}